All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
BadDateFormatException
A RuntimeException thrown in cases of a bad date format provided by the user.
ComponentLogger
AOP-enabled class that logs all calls to public methods of repositories annotated with Logged.
Constants
Various global constants used by our app.
CryptoDirectoryParser
A utility class responsible for parsing a given directory of CSV files with crypto prices.
CryptoPrice
A simple POJO to represent the price of a particular crypto at a certain timestamp.
CryptoPriceAggregateStatsMiner
A Runnable that queries the DatabaseConnection object with which it is constructed for aggregate stats of the provided crypto.
CryptoPriceFileReader
Reads a CSV file in memory and returns a List of CryptoPrice instances, one per row of the CSV.
CryptoPricePersister
A Runnable which: Uses the DatabaseConnection object provided at construction to create the table corresponding to the File parameter object's name. Uses the provided CryptoPriceFileReader to read the file in memory. Uses the DatabaseConnection object to persist the file rows on the DB table just created. Once finished, it counts down the provided CountDownLatch instance.
CryptoPricesForDateMiner
Queries the DatabaseConnection object provided at construction for the prices of the provided cryptocurrency for the provided day, and stores the normalized price in the provided ConcurrentMap instance.
CryptoPriceStats
A class that holds aggregate stats of a particular crypto in memory.
CryptoRecController
A RestController responsible for serving up endpoints, receiving and sending data to the user.
CryptoRecService
Service layer class that supports the operations of CryptoRecController.
CryptoRecServiceApplication
 
DatabaseConnection
An interface for communicating with a relational database.
DatabaseConnectionImpl
An implementation of DatabaseConnection that performs batch inserts for DatabaseConnection.insertAllCryptoPrices(String, List).
DateOutOfStoredRangeException
A RuntimeException thrown by our code when the user provides a day to search crypto stats for which is out of the range of dates that we have stored information for.
EmailAlreadyInDatabaseException
A RuntimeException thrown when the user tries to register with a username that already exists in the database.
ExceptionAdvice
RestControllerAdvice for all our custom exceptions, and some non-custom ones, too.
ExceptionMessageContainer
A simple message container to allow exception handlers to be rendered by clients in JSON format.
InMemoryAggregateStats
An in-memory " database " of crypto stats with thread-safe structural modification operations.
JwtAuthenticationController
Controller for user authentication.
JwtAuthenticationEntryPoint
Defines the default API response for unauthenticated calls to any endpoint.
JwtAuthenticationService
A service class that provides a single authentication method for users.
JwtRequest
Simple POJO for defining a user request for a JWT token.
JwtRequestFilter
A OncePerRequestFilter that filters every incoming request to make sure that it is properly authenticated with an unexpired JWT token.
JwtResponse
Simple POJO that defines the API's response to the user for a JWT token request.
JwtTokenUtil
Various utilities for generating and parsing JWTs.
JwtUserDetailsService
Service class that talks to the database to retrieve and store user information.
Loc
Simple enum used by MethodLoggingMessages to log entrance or exit from methods.
Logged
An empty interface that we decorate classes for which we want to log the entrance and exit (gracious or otherwise) to its methods.
MethodLoggingMessages
final class whose static methods are used by ComponentLogger classes to log their messages.
OpenAPI30Configuration
A configuration class that configures the OpenAPI 3 components for our app.
PasswordEncoderConfig
Defines a Spring Bean of type PasswordEncoder for the various components to use.
PreloadDatabase
On-disk and in-memory database pre-loader.
SecurityConfig
Spring Security configuration for API.
SortOrder
A simple enum used by various methods that want to designate ascending or descending sorting order.
StatsCalculationService
Computes the aggregate stats for all provided cryptos and loads them to the in-memory database instance provided at construction.
TimeZoneConfig
Configuring the default timezone used by the Spring app.
UnsupportedCryptoException
A RuntimeException thrown whenever the user supplies a crypto with a name that we do not (yet) support.
UserDto
DTO class for Users.
UserEntity
Database object for application users.
UserRepository
A JpaRepository used to persist UserEntity instances.
